1608":"9. december 1608","1668":"1668","1666":"1666","1600":"1600","1620":"1620","1587":"1587","Abt 1574":"omkring 1574","1575":"1575","1585":"1585","1574":"1574","1608":"1608","27 July 1600":"27. juli 1600","1637":"1637","1648":"1648","1603":"1603","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","Stourton, Wiltshire, England":"Stourton, Wiltshire, England","Stourton, Stourton with Gasper, Wiltshire Unitary authority, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Stourton, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"Abt 1574–1637":"circa 1574–1637","1575–1648":"1575–1648","1600–1666":"1600–1666","1603–1668":"1603–1668","1608–Male":"1608–Overleden","1574–1637":"1574–1637","9 Dec 1608":"9 december 1608","1668":"1668","1666":"1666","1600":"1600","1620":"1620","1587":"1587","Abt 1574":"circa 1574","1575":"1575","1585":"1585","1574":"1574","1608":"1608","27 July 1600":"27 juli 1600","1637":"1637","1648":"1648","1603":"1603","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","Stourton, Wiltshire, England":"Stourton, Wiltshire, England","Stourton, Stourton with Gasper, Wiltshire Unitary authority, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Stourton, Wiltshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1574–1637":"about 1574–1637","1575–1648":"1575–1648","1600–1666":"1600–1666","1603–1668":"1603–1668","1608–Male":"1608–Deceased","1574–1637":"1574–1637","9 Dec 1608":"9 December 1608","1668":"1668","1666":"1666","1600":"1600","1620":"1620","1587":"1587","Abt 1574":"about 1574","1575":"1575","1585":"1585","1574":"1574","1608":"1608","27 July 1600":"27 July 1600","1637":"1637","1648":"1648","1603":"1603","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","Stourton, Wiltshire, England":"Stourton, Wiltshire, England","Stourton, Stourton with Gasper, Wiltshire Unitary authority, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Stourton, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Godfrey","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): from the Norman personal name <i>Godefrei</i>, <i>Godefroi(s)</i>, composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>god</i>, <i>got</i> ‘god’ + <i>frid(u)</i>, <i>fred</i> ‘peace’. See also   Jeffrey  .","Irish: shortened and Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Gothraidh</b> or <b>Ó Gothraidh</b>, ‘descendant of <i>Gothfrith</i>’, an Old Norse personal name often Anglicized as <i>Godfrey</i>. Compare   McGorry  ,   McCaffrey  .","History: An Irish family of the name Godfrey originated in Romney, Kent. The first of them to settle in Ireland was Colonel John Godfrey, who was rewarded with lands in Kerry for his services in the 1641 rebellion. Godefroy, Lord of Normanville, from Normandy, was married in Trois-Rivières, QC, in 1636. He was captured by the Iroquois in 1652. His brother, Lord of Linctot, from Rouen, was also married in 1636 in Trois-Rivières, and lived from 1629 to 1632 among the Hurons. Another Godefroy, from Paris, was a trader and interpreter from 1623."],"variants":[{"name":"Geurts","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Florent, Jacques.","Dutch and Flemish: patronymic from a vernacular shortened form of the ancient Germanic personal names <i>Godevaard</i> (see   Godfrey  ) or <i>Godert</i> (see   Gotthardt  )."]},{"name":"Good","meanings":["English: nickname from Middle English <i>gode</i> ‘good’ (Old English <i>gōd</i>).","English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Gode</i>, representing either Old English <i>Goda</i> (male) or <i>Gode</i> (female), in part a byname and in part a short form of various compound names with the first element <i>gōd</i>, or perhaps a pet form of Old French names in <i>God-</i> such as   Godfrey  .","Americanized form (translation into English) of German   Gut   and   Guth  , or Dutch <b>Goed</b> and   Goede  ."]},{"name":"Goffredo","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Alfonso, Angelo, Carmine, Carolina, Marina, Mario, Nicola, Savino, Vito.","Italian: from the personal name <i>Goffredo</i>, an equivalent of   Godfrey  ."]},{"name":"Jeffrey","meanings":["English and Scottish: from the common Middle English and Older Scots personal name <i>Geffrey</i>, a borrowing of Old French <i>Geuffrei</i>, <i>Jeufrei</i>, <i>Jefrei</i>, <i>Gosfrei</i>, <i>Jofrei</i>. The principal source of the Old French forms was probably ancient Germanic <i>Gautfrid</i>, from an ethnic name + <i>frithu</i> ‘peace’. It was commonly Latinized in early documents as <i>Gaufridus</i> or <i>Galfridus</i>, but also as <i>Goisfridus</i> or <i>Gosfridus</i>. Anglo-Norman French <i>Jofreith</i>, <i>Jofrei</i> lies behind the English surnames <i>Joffrey</i> and <i>Joffray</i>, which are recorded in the late nineteenth century, but may now be extinct."]}]},{"name":"Walter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, superseding the native Old English form, <i>Wealdhere</i>. It was a very popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705207,"age":11,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705208,"age":13,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705210,"age":26,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705212,"age":46,"year":"1620","julianDay":2312753,"title":"The Pilgrims Board the Mayflower","description":"\"The Pilgrims boarded the Mayflower in search of religious freedom in the New World in September 1620. The Mayflower set sail from Plymouth, England, with 102 passengers, 40 of whom called themselves \"\"Saints.\"\" After two stormy months at sea, the ship reached the New World. Nearly half of the group died during their first winter due to malnutrition and the harsh New England winter.\"","url":"https://www.themayflowersociety.org/the-pilgrims/pilgrim-history","urlTitle":"The Mayflower Society - Pilgrim History","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Walter Godfrey was born about 1574, in Stourton, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son and 2 daughters with Emily Elizabeth Cleverly. He died in 1637, in Wiltshire, England, at the age of 64."},"et":{"Abt 1574–1637":"umbes 1574–1637","1575–1648":"1575–1648","1600–1666":"1600–1666","1603–1668":"1603–1668","1608–Male":"1608–Surnud","1574–1637":"1574–1637","9 Dec 1608":"9. detsember 1608","1668":"1668","1666":"1666","1600":"1600","1620":"1620","1587":"158